      "body" : "It's infeasible (with at least cryptographic hardness) to identify every unsatisfiable transaction; just catching a few classes is unlikely to save someone unless it was especially easy to hit (and if so perhaps should be fixed at the source).  That it catches some but not all might give a false sense of security.\r\n\r\nI think a more general script-lint would be interesting, but probably shouldn't be part of the rpc.",
